parameters: An old envelope sits in the dusty corner of the lost and found.
I remember Mom getting these in the mail before my library card expired.
They usually had event announcements or policy change notices.
Something was left under the envelope.
It's a cheap lighter that someone probably got at a gas station.
I take the\c[4] Lighter\c[0] and pocket it.
